{"TopicId":163106,"ForumId":15,"TopicTitle":"Apply polar distortion to images in GIMP","CreatedByName":"ModerndayLink","CreatedById":173044,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-07-10T19:19:24Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"ModerndayLink","CreatedById":173044,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-07-10T19:19:24Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTitle speaks for itself, I have a texture for a planet I\u0027m making and I cant seem to figure out how to apply polar distortion to the texture in GIMP,\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nso does anyone know how to do that?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Galileo","CreatedById":150430,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-07-10T19:29:39Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFilter\u0026gt;Distorts\u0026gt;Polar Coordinates\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nedit the pole, then\u00A0\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#272a34;\u0022\u003EFilter\u0026gt;Distorts\u0026gt;Polar Coordinates and deselect the To Polar option. This will revert back to a rectangular map with a distorted polar area.\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#272a34;\u0022\u003Eflip the image and repeat.\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-07-10T19:33:11Z\u0022 title=\u002207/10/2017 07:33  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EJuly 10, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by Galileo\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"ModerndayLink","CreatedById":173044,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-07-10T20:53:11Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223116849\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022163106\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221499714979\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022150430\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Galileo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, Galileo said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nedit the pole\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIs there a way to apply distortion without editing the pole (or basically just stretch the texture without editing anything by hand?) because I am still a Noob when it comes to drawing, and the planets texture was just generated using noise.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"JadeOfMaar","CreatedById":167617,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-07-10T21:51:33Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223116849\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022163106\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221499714979\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022150430\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Galileo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, Galileo said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFilter\u0026gt;Distorts\u0026gt;Polar Coordinates\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nedit the pole, then\u00A0\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#272a34;\u0022\u003EFilter\u0026gt;Distorts\u0026gt;Polar Coordinates and deselect the To Polar option. This will revert back to a rectangular map with a distorted polar area.\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#272a34;\u0022\u003Eflip the image and repeat.\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m assuming the process here blows Photoshop\u0027s polar filter out of the water?\u00A0afaik Photoshop\u0027s one is a mule, not even a one-trick pony. There is so much I want to and/or must learn.\u00A0\u003Cs\u003EAnd I\u0027m kinda entrenched in Photoshop.\u003C/s\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-07-10T21:51:56Z\u0022 title=\u002207/10/2017 09:51  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EJuly 10, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by JadeOfMaar\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Galileo","CreatedById":150430,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-07-10T22:09:06Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223117005\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022163106\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221499723493\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022167617\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022JadeOfMaar\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n30 minutes ago, JadeOfMaar said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m assuming the process here blows Photoshop\u0027s polar filter out of the water?\u00A0afaik Photoshop\u0027s one is a mule, not even a one-trick pony. There is so much I want to and/or must learn.\u00A0\u003Cs\u003EAnd I\u0027m kinda entrenched in Photoshop.\u003C/s\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNope it\u0027s the exact same in photoshop, nearly exact steps need to be taken in photoshop. I always go to photoshop first, Gimp is growing on\u00A0me though for certain things.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223116938\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022163106\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221499719991\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022173044\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022ModerndayLink64\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, ModerndayLink64 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIs there a way to apply distortion without editing the pole (or basically just stretch the texture without editing anything by hand?) because I am still a Noob when it comes to drawing, and the planets texture was just generated using noise.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNo,\u00A0that\u0027s the only way to achieve good results.\u00A0The way you are asking about will result in awful looking textures.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-07-10T22:22:19Z\u0022 title=\u002207/10/2017 10:22  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EJuly 10, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by Galileo\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"JadeOfMaar","CreatedById":167617,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-07-10T22:15:36Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223117031\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022163106\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221499724546\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022150430\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Galileo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n6 minutes ago, Galileo said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNope it\u0027s the exact same in photoshop, nearly exact steps need to be taken in photoshop. I always go to photoshop first, Gimp is growing in me though for certain things.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m about to head home now. I must definitely try this. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:o\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/ZNGIcon2.png\u0022 title=\u0022:o\u0022\u003E\u00A0Oh, does it work for skyboxes too?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223117031\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022163106\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221499724546\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022150430\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Galileo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n6 minutes ago, Galileo said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\ngrowing in me\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou might wanna see a doctor for that.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-07-10T22:15:59Z\u0022 title=\u002207/10/2017 10:15  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EJuly 10, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by JadeOfMaar\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Galileo","CreatedById":150430,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-07-10T22:24:37Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223117041\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022163106\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221499724936\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022167617\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022JadeOfMaar\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n6 minutes ago, JadeOfMaar said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOh, does it work for skyboxes too?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNo because skyboxes are applied differently in game they are in fact, a box that we fly around in. So, no poles.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"ModerndayLink","CreatedById":173044,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-07-10T22:59:08Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223117031\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022163106\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221499724546\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022150430\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Galileo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n49 minutes ago, Galileo said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNope it\u0027s the exact same in photoshop, nearly exact steps need to be taken in photoshop. I always go to photoshop first, Gimp is growing on\u00A0me though for certain things.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNo,\u00A0that\u0027s the only way to achieve good results.\u00A0The way you are asking about will result in awful looking textures.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\noh ok, time to learn how to use gimp.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Galileo","CreatedById":150430,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-07-10T23:22:52Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223117090\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022163106\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221499727548\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022173044\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022ModerndayLink64\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n19 minutes ago, ModerndayLink64 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\noh ok, time to learn how to use gimp.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFor this particular situation, I recommend the clone tool then blending it in\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}